Commitment to the Community:
Health, Safety, Security, and Environment (HSSE) is a core of the Facility and organization. The Facility will operate in the safest possible manner that is consistent with our values and commitment to the community and coordination with the local response teams. The Facility complies with the highest HSSE standards, ensuring targets are set and performance is benchmarked to achieve continuous improvement and best in performance.
Policies:
• Compliance with all applicable environmental, health and safety performance;
• Continual improvement in health, safety, and security performance with the goal of zero injuries;
• Continual reduction of the environmental impact of our operations;
• Design and operation of our facilities in a manner that protects the environment and the health, safety and security of our employees, contractors, and the public;
• Development and production of products that can be manufactured, distributed, used and recycled and disposed of in a safe, secure, and sustainable manner;
• Existing and new EH&S risks are understood and managed through the Risk Management Processes’
• Transparent discussion of our environmental, health, and safety practices and performance;
• All Incidents can be prevented;
• All levels of Management are accountable for safety and must lead by example;
• Each employee must be trained and is committed to planning and working safely and to protecting the safety of others and the environment;
• Employees participate fully in all elements of the safety program;
• Everyone looks out for each other;
• Everyone has stop work authority; and
• Zero tolerance for safety breaches.
Facility Description and Substance Handled:
The Facility stores Anhydrous Ammonia, which is a chemical used to manufacture common products, mostly fertilizers.

